cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with semantic labeling of RGB-D scenes, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. It also incorporates deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for end-to-end training, which is a popular technique in computer vision research. 

It could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as semantic labeling of RGB-D scenes is crucial to many intelligent applications including perceptual robotics. 

The paper also proposes a novel Long Short-Term Memorized Fusion (LSTM-F) Model, which involves capturing and fusing contextual information from multiple channels of photometric and depth data. This could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper uses a bi-directional propagation technique to obtain true 2D global contexts, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
